The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, August 15, 2004 				Metro Recommends
 THE VCD 
	(MusicWorld, Rs 99 to Rs 125) l The collection that you cant do without. Period. Just pick it all up blindfolded and play it at leisure. If all you want to do is have a laugh, go for the shorts, but if you want a love affair with The Tramp that lingers, pick up City Lights, Modern Times and, of course, Limelight (above). THE EVENT
	(Crossword, August 18 and 21) l Kicked off by Bombay Vikings on August 13, the fun-packed music extravaganza runs for 15 days. Highlights for the week are rock bands Chandrabindoo (August 18) and Krosswindz (August 21).THE MATCH				 																																	(Star Sports, Sunday, 8.30 pm)				 																																	lIt doesnt get bigger than this for a season-opener. Chelseas new boss Jose Mourinhos quest to turn big spending into silverware could get a dream start with a win at home, as Alex Ferguson kicks off the League with an injury-hit Man U line-up. Watch out for Chelseas record signing, Didier Drogba (below).
